Three Uyghurs who tried to sneak into Vietnam from southwest China have clashed with policemen in the border city of Pingxiang, in Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
Two of the Uyghurs were shot dead and one escaped.
Authorities said police discovered the trio trying to cross the border on Sunday night. The police stopped their car, but they resisted arrest.
After clashing with police, two of them were shot dead. One ran into a residential area.
Police said the fugitive is 1.75 meters tall, was wearing a red T-shirt and jeans, and speaks the Uighur language.
Police called on residents to be alert and call the police to notify them of any sightings.



